description: Deck data ↔ UI flag rendering must have an end-to-end snapshot test. Whenever a card-data flag (`unique`, `classCard`, `permEquipment`, `isPermanentEvent`, `magicType`, etc.) is consumed by a renderer to draw a badge / pill / overlay, there must be a test that asserts the EXPECTED set of cards in the deck carry that flag. Without this test, anyone deleting a single `unique: true,` line silently breaks the UI badge for that card with no signal.
alwaysApply: true
